  "issue_number": 272,
  "issue_title": "Feature: improve local and offline runtime indicators",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\nTouchPilot has local router/model status text, but the product UI does not strongly communicate when work is local-only, when LiteRT is available, or when deterministic fallback is active.\n\n## Proposed behavior\nImprove runtime indicators across Chat and Settings so users can understand the current local/offline execution mode at a glance.\n\n## Goal to reach\nThe user can tell whether TouchPilot is using local router, local model, fallback mode, and whether cloud services are involved.\n\n## Minimal scope\n- Improve the existing Chat runtime/skill strip or equivalent status surface.\n- Improve Settings runtime status copy/card.\n- Clearly show local router vs local model availability.\n- Clearly show local-only/no-cloud behavior for core runtime.\n- Reuse existing LocalModelStatus and AgentProviderMode data.\n\n## Out of scope\n- New runtime backends.\n- Benchmark UI from Milestone 8.\n- Cloud provider redesign.\n- Model training or model asset changes.\n\n## User workflow\nA user opens Chat or Settings and can immediately understand the active runtime mode and locality.\n\n## Local-first impact\nThis supports user trust by making local-first operation visible.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\nRuntime indicators should not claim cloud is impossible for optional integrations; they should distinguish core local runtime from separately configured integrations.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-16T03:24:33.000Z",
